  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "GitHub is one of the most popular platforms for version control and collaboration, and it is used by a wide range of companies and startups across various industries. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### Large Companies\n1. **Microsoft** - Owner of GitHub since 2018, Microsoft uses it extensively for its own projects.\n2. **Google** - Uses GitHub for many of its open-source projects.\n3. **Facebook** - Hosts several of its open-source projects on GitHub.\n4. **Apple** - Uses GitHub for some of its open-source initiatives.\n5. **Amazon** - Utilizes GitHub for various open-source projects.\n6. **Netflix** - Shares many of its tools and libraries on GitHub.\n7. **IBM** - Hosts numerous open-source projects on GitHub.\n8. **Twitter** - Uses GitHub for its open-source contributions.\n9. **Uber** - Shares many of its internal tools and libraries on GitHub.\n10. **Airbnb** - Uses GitHub for open-source projects and internal collaboration.\n\n### Startups\n1. **Stripe** - Known for its developer-friendly tools, Stripe uses GitHub for collaboration.\n2. **Slack** - Uses GitHub for internal projects and open-source contributions.\n3. **Coinbase** - Utilizes GitHub for its blockchain and cryptocurrency-related projects.\n4. **GitLab** - While it has its own platform, GitLab also uses GitHub for certain projects.\n5. **Figma** - Uses GitHub for version control and collaboration.\n6. **Airtable** - Utilizes GitHub for various projects and open-source initiatives.\n7. **Notion** - Uses GitHub for internal development and open-source projects.\n8. **Plaid** - Uses GitHub for its financial technology projects.\n9. **Dropbox** - Uses GitHub for open-source contributions.\n10. **DigitalOcean** - Utilizes GitHub for its cloud infrastructure projects.\n\n### Open Source Projects\n1. **Linux** - The Linux kernel has its development on GitHub.\n2. **Kubernetes** - The popular container orchestration tool is hosted on GitHub.\n3. **TensorFlow** - Google's machine learning framework is on GitHub.\n4. **VS Code** - Microsoft's popular code editor is developed and hosted on GitHub.\n5. **React** - Facebook's JavaScript library for building user interfaces is on GitHub.\n6. **Angular** - Google's web application framework is hosted on GitHub.\n7. **Node.js** - The JavaScript runtime is developed on GitHub.\n8. **Mozilla Firefox** - Many components and tools for Firefox are on GitHub.\n9. **WordPress** - The popular content management system has its development on GitHub.\n10. **Homebrew** - The macOS package manager is hosted on GitHub.\n\nGitHub is a versatile platform that serves a wide array of needs, from version control and collaboration to open-source contributions, making it a critical tool for both established companies and emerging startups.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
